From: GUO Zihua <guozihua@huawei.com>
Date: Fri, 11 Nov 2022 18:13:17 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] integrity: Fix memory leakage in keyring allocation error
 path
Git-commit: 39419ef7af0916cc3620ecf1ed42d29659109bf3
Patch-mainline: v6.2-rc1
References: CVE-2022-50395 bsc#1250211

[ Adapted backport, before refactoring the 'restriction' is still not freed on
 the error path. ]

Key restriction is allocated in integrity_init_keyring(). However, if
keyring allocation failed, it is not freed, causing memory leaks.

Fixes: 2b6aa412ff23 ("KEYS: Use structure to capture key restriction function and data")
Signed-off-by: GUO Zihua <guozihua@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Mimi Zohar <zohar@linux.ibm.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 security/integrity/digsig.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/security/integrity/digsig.c
+++ b/security/integrity/digsig.c
@@ -106,6 +106,7 @@ int __init integrity_init_keyring(const
 		pr_info("Can't allocate %s keyring (%d)\n",
 			keyring_name[id], err);
 		keyring[id] = NULL;
+		kfree(restriction);
 	}
 	return err;
 }
